Scan File Name: 		ARM-2023-129-PS SCAN 1

Feature / Description: 	ARM-2023-129-PS



Analysis / Interpretation: 

Code E internal wall loss from erosion can be found at the 12 o’clock position of the scan.
The lowest reading is located at 17mm downstream from the centre point and 1mm circumferentially North from the 12 o’clock position. No coating is present, so the 1st echo has been used.

1st echo reading: 14.06mm

A Velocity Correction Factor of 0.976 was used to calculate the final reading.

14.06 x 0.976 = 13.72mm – Code E

C-scan is on the next page for reference.

Vessel Coverage: 
The overall target coverage of the vessel shell was 50%. >65% coverage achieved. Please note the vessel remained online during inspection and as such the channel side was not inspected due to high operating temperature.
 
Provision of datum points  
 
Vessel Shell: 
Index (X): The index datum is CW01, with the positive increment heading Eastwards along the vessel. 
 
Scan (Y): The scan datum is the vessel's 12 o'clock position, with the 3 o'clock position at platform South and the 9 o'clock position at platform North. 
 
Scan sensitivity 
A minimum scan sensitivity of reference +14dB has been used. 
 
Restrictions 
Scan Restrictions included saddles, nozzles, nameplate, and external pipework & instrumentation (see scan log for further details).

Scan File Name: 		V-2801-1 S-3000-4320 I-900-1650 pit-1

Feature / Description: 	Shell Anomaly Code D



Analysis / Interpretation:

Pitting was on the lower section of the shell. Location (3484mm from North and 945mm from CW1). 

This was previously located in 2022 and was repeated to ascertain any further degradation. 

Previous result was 39.3mm Anomaly code C. 

Minimum wall thickness measured: 38.82mm. Anomaly Code D.

All measurements have coating correction applied.

Circled in yellow are 2 other areas of pitting noted. Anomaly code A.

Feature / Description: 	Upper section anomaly code B.



Analysis / Interpretation:

Pitting was on the upper section of the shell. Location (5176mm from North Datum and 3109mm from CW1). 

Minimum wall thickness measured: 39.83mm. Anomaly Code B.

All measurements have coating correction applied.

Summary
As part of a vessel NII on H-1701-1 in accordance with work pack NEV-2025-2651-WP-INSP, flange face PAUT inspection was requested on selected nozzle flanges. This inspection was to detect any corrosion/ erosion around the internal flange face and internal bore. Please see below for requested work scope areas and results

This inspection was conducted in accordance with MAI-P-NDT-008-PAFF-R1 flange face procedure and Technique sheet- MAI-NDT-020-PAUT

Results
No significant internal corrosion or indications were found on the flanges inspected

Restrictions
Due to the size and geometry of the flanges and attached flange bolts, Taper scans could not be conducted on any of the selected nozzles, only Rim and bolt face scans were conducted. N1 & N2 Restricted for PAUT.
